hardstatus string '%{= kR}%?[%0`]%?%?[%5`]%?%?[%1`]%?%?[%2`]%?%?[%3`]%?%?[%4`]%?%?[%6`]%?%{= kG}[%= %{g}%?%-w%?%{r}(%{W}%n*%t%?(%u)%?%{r})%{G}%?%+w%?%= %{G}]'
# My GNU Screen Hardstatus explanation:
# Set my hardstatus colour to Red on Black for my backticks. All my backticks will be wrapped inside [Red Sq. Brackets] if they return anything.
# My Backticks are documented below. They return a few Unicodes, based on my local system status
# Then set my hardstatus colour to Green on Black for my open sessions. 
# My Session hardstatus will be center-aligned
# My currently focused session will be wrapped in (Red Brackets) and the text will be white instead of green


### Defaults ###
defscrollback 10000
shelltitle "b0rk"
termcapinfo xterm* ti@:te@

#shell -bash
startup_message off

### Keyboard Shortcuts ###
bindkey ^[[1;5D prev # change window with ctrl-left (Un*x)
bindkey ^[[1;5C next # change window with ctrl-right (Un*x)
bindkey "^[[D" prev  # change window with ctrl-left (Putty)
bindkey "^[[C" next  # change window with ctrl-right (Putty)

# We need to check if the task has been started at least once to prevent things getting stuck    
bash -c '[ ! -r ~/.taskrc ] && yes | task > /dev/null 2>&1'

### Backticks ###
#Shows [ðŸ’½] at screen hardstatus, when one of my local disks is 90%+ filled
backtick 0 60 60 bash -c 'df -h | egrep -q '\''9[0-9]+%|100%'\'' && echo ðŸ’½'
#Shows [ðŸ] at the screen hardstatus, when my local free mem is less than 300MB
backtick 1 5 5 bash -c 'if [ $(free -m | grep Mem |  awk '\''{print $4}'\'') -le 300 ]; then echo ðŸ; fi'
#Shows [ðŸ˜©] at the screen hardstatus, when my local free swap is less than 300MB
backtick 2 5 5 bash -c 'if [ $(free -m | grep Swap |  awk '\''{print $4}'\'') -le 300 ]; then echo ðŸ˜©; fi'
#Shows [ðŸ“¨] at the screen hardstatus, when I have new tickets assigned. (You should have a cronjob putting the number of tickets in ~/TicketsAssigned)
backtick 3 5 5 bash -c 'if [ $(cat ~/TicketsAssigned) -ge 1 ]; then echo ðŸ“¨; fi'
#Shows A set of unicodes for TaskWarrior state. Screen doesn't like multiline splits so all in one big line
backtick 4 5 5 bash -c 'if [ `task +READY +OVERDUE count` -gt "0" ]; then echo "â˜ ï¸ "; elif [ `task +READY +DUETODAY count` -gt "0" ]; then echo "ðŸ˜±"; elif [ `task +READY +TOMORROW count` -gt "0" ]; then echo "ðŸ“…"; elif [ `task +READY urgency \> 10 count` -gt "0" ]; then echo "â—"; fi'
#Shows [ðŸ”¥] at screen hardstatus, when my CPU load average is higher than 8. Increase this number to something that makes sense for the amount of CPUs in your system
backtick 5 5 5 bash -c 'if (( $(echo "$(cat /proc/loadavg | awk '\''{print $1}'\'') > 8" | bc -l) )); then echo ðŸ”¥; fi'
#Shows [âš¡] at the screen hardstatus, when my group's queue has a priority ticket, and [ðŸ“¬] when it is overflowing. (You should have a cronjob putting the number of tickets in the files referenced below)
backtick 6 5 5 bash -c 'if [ $(cat ~/TicketsGroupPriority) -ge 1 ]; then echo âš¡; elif [ $(cat ~/TicketsGroupAssigned) -ge 10 ]; then echo ðŸ“¬; fi'
 

### Logging ###
deflog on
logfile $HOME/.Screenlogs/screenlog-%t_%Y-%m-%d_%0c%s.log
logtstamp on

### Default screens ###
screen -t STFU	0
screen -t JUMP	1
screen -t RTFM	2

